BankAmerica Corp said it completedthe sale of its Consumer Trust Services division to Well Fargoand Co &lt;WFC>, a transaction that will result in a secondquarter pre-tax gain of more than 75 mln dlrs.    The sale will not affect the services the bank willcontinue providing to institutional customers through itsEmployee Benefit Trust Services Division, BankAmerica alsosaid.    In a separate announcement, Wells Fargo said theacquisition will increase the amount of personal trust assetsit administers to 25 billion dlrs.    Last December BankAmerica and Wells Fargo announced adefinitive agreement on the sale at a price of about 100 mlndlrs, subject to adjustment. Reuter&#3;